0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14. </div><div class="t m7c6 x4e h27 y1fdb ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What did the soldiers then do? What did His </div><div class="t m434 x27 h27 y168c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">disciples do ? John 18: 12 ; Mark 14 : 50. </div><div class="t me4 x18 h27 y16ff ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">15. </div><div class="t m7ae x60 h27 y16b7 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What befell a young man who followed Jesus? </div><div class="t m6a9 x27 h27 y1850 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 14: 51, 52. Note 4. </div><div class="t me4 x18 h27 y68d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16. </div><div class="t m9e3 x60 h27 y1918 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where did the soldiers take Jesus? What counsel </div><div class="t m907 x27 h27 y18cd ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">had Caiaphas given? John 18 : 12-14. Note 5. </div><div class="t me4 x18 h27 y1594 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17. </div><div class="t m85 x4e h27 y353 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What question was asked Jesus? What was His </div><div class="t m14b x27 h27 y1a5f ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reply? Verses 19-21. </div><div class="t me4 x18 h27 y19f8 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18. </div><div class="t mf2 x4e h27 y19f8 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What indignity </div><div class="t m168e x32 h4 y1637 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was </div><div class="t m11c x98 h27 y1a3c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">shown Jesus by one of the </div><div class="t m3b1 x27 h27 y21e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">officers? What was His response? Verses 22, 23. </div><div class="t me4 x18 h27 y1598 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19. </div><div class="t m1489 x4e h27 y693 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where did Annas send Jesus? Who followed </div><div class="t m1aa8 x27 h27 yc32 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him? How? Verse 24; Luke 22: 54. </div><div class="t ma59 x1d h4 yf61 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Notes </div><div class="t mb16 x14 h4 y161e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. &quot;As these words [&quot; I am He&quot;] were spoken, the angel who </div><div class="t mbe4 x27 h4 y17a8 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">had lately ministered to Jesus, moved between Him and the </div><div class="t m119 x27 h4 y49f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mob. A divine light illuminated the Saviour&apos;s face, and a dove-like </div><div class="t m169b x27 h4 y19cc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">form overshadowed Him. In the presence of this divine glory, </div><div class="t m290 x27 h4 y17e0 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the murderous throng could not stand for a moment. They stag-</div><div class="t m178 x27 h4 y1947 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gered back. Priests, elders, soldiers, and eyea Judas, fell as dead </div><div class="t m836 x27 h4 y1a18 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">men to the ground. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
